'''La Bella Durmiente''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for [[Sleeping Beauty]])''',''' also known as '''Puma Ringri''' (possibly from [[Quechua language|Quechua]] ''puma'' [[cougar]], puma, ''rinri'' ear,<ref>Teofilo Laime Ajacopa, Diccionario Bilingüe Iskay simipi yuyayk'ancha, La Paz, 2007 (Quechua-Spanish dictionary)</ref> "puma ear"), is a mountain and prominent feature of [[Tingo Maria National Park|Tingo María National Park]], in the region of [[Huánuco Region|Huánuco]], [[Peru]].<ref name="sernanp">{{cite web|url=http://www.sernanp.gob.pe/tingo-maria|title=Tingo María|publisher=SERNANP|language=Spanish|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref><ref name="mincetur">{{cite web|url=http://ficha.sigmincetur.mincetur.gob.pe/index.aspx?cod_Ficha=4831|title=La Bella Durmiente|first=|date=|website=|publisher=mincetur|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=April 29, 2017}}</ref> It is located in the district of [[Mariano Damaso Beraun District|Mariano Damaso]], [[Leoncio Prado Province]], [[Huánuco Region|Huánuco]] and reaches an elevation of {{convert|1805|m|ft|0}}.<ref name="mincetur" />

== Name ==
The name comes from the shape of the mountain, which resembles a woman lying down, and is present in a local folktale.<ref name="mincetur" /><ref>{{Cite book|title=Tingo Maria National Park - 50 years|last=|first=|publisher=SERNANP|year=2014|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=English, Spanish}}</ref>

